A tibble with the results of the 2017 general election.

A tibble with Great Britain constituencies results from the 2017 general election. This data can be linked to 2011 census information in bes_2015.

ge_2017

Format

A tibble, containing 632 row and 58 columns.

pano

Press Association Constituency ID. Numeric.

onsconst_id

ONS Constituency ID. Character.

constituency_name

Constituency Name. Factor.

country

Country. Factor.

region

Region. Factor.

constituency_type

County or Borough Constituency. Factor.

winner_17

2017 Winning party. Factor.

electorate_17

2017 Size of electorate. Numeric.

total_vote_17

2017 Total number of votes cast. Numeric.

rejected_vote_17

2017 Number of rejected ballots. Numeric.

majority_17

2017 Majority. Numeric.

majority_17

2017 Majority. Numeric.

turnout_17

2017 Turnout. Numeric.

seat_change_1517

2017 winning party gain from 2015 winning party. Factor.

con_vote_17

2017 Conservative number of votes. Numeric.

lab_vote_17

2017 Labour number of votes. Numeric.

ld_vote_17

2017 Liberal Democrat number of votes. Numeric.

ukip_vote_17

2017 United Kingdom Independence Party (UKIP) number of votes. Numeric.

green_vote_17

2017 Green Party number of votes. Numeric.

snp_vote_17

2017 Scottish National Party (SNP) number of votes. Numeric.

2017 Plaid Cymru number of votes. Numeric.
